# Backend Rules

## Structure

```
routes/ → validators/ (Zod) → services/ → repositories/interfaces/ → repositories/drizzle/
domain/ = pure functions, no db imports
container/ = only place that instantiates concrete classes
```

## Example service

```typescript
export class EmployeeService {
  constructor(private readonly employees: IEmployeeRepository) {}
}
```

## Tests (order)

1. `domain/*.test.ts` — pure logic
2. `services/*.test.ts` — mock repos
3. `repositories/**/*.test.ts` — `:memory:` SQLite
4. `tests/*.integration.test.ts` — Supertest

## Compensation repository

```typescript
interface ICompensationRepository {
  insert(record: NewCompensationRecord): Promise<CompensationRecord>;
  findByEmployeeId(id: string): Promise<CompensationRecord[]>;
  // NO update() or delete()
}
```
